value.0: Ah, yes, hello there. I am, eh, Hemmel Masterson. This is my wife Agnes, and our manservent Morden.
I wonder, by chance, if you've seen a man named Jalek? He has an amulet of mine and he, ah, seems to have forgotten us.
Forgotten? I TOLD you he was not to be trusted.
I'm quite aware of what you said, my dear. Now, if you will just let me speak to this nice <man/woman>.
Eh, yes, very well. Goodbye. We'll just... wait here for mister Jalek then. Yes. That's what we'll do.
Well, it's embarrassing. You see, we were led to believe that passage out of Neverwinter could be had here. We were fleeing the quarantine.
I arranged for transport that would leave from the docks. I traded an heirloom amulet to a half-orc man who swore he was honest.
Hemmel, I can swear that you are competent, but that doesn't make it true.
My wife may disagree with my appraisal of him, but he swore he would return.
Yes... that I did. The gentleman Jalek said he was soon to come into his own ship, and he would take us out of Neverwinter, in exchange for the amulet.
Err... a strapping, if brutish gent. Jalek was his name. He said he was soon to come into his own ship.
Probably stealing that as well. Honestly, Hemmel, you can be such a fool.
My dear, he seemed honest enough. He may yet return. It has only been... a day...
Please, I hope you will reconsider. This Jalek, he has taken advantage of me and I can't do anything about it except point you in his direction.
I suppose I could manage some form of payment. I'll have to see the amulet first, of course. I've already been swindled once.
I would be most appreciative if you could. Mr Jalek does appear to be... taking an inordinate amount of time.
Please, return my amulet if you find it. It will have the Masterson crest. I've given up on breaking quarantine; I just want back what's mine.
Very little, I'm afraid. I came here... well... I came here hoping to circumvent the quarantine on Neverwinter.
Hello again, <FirstName>. I hope you have good news for me? I've seen no sign of Jalek or my amulet.
Oh... Please do return when you have news of my amulet.
If you need, though I don't know if there's anything else I can add.
Wonderful! Snatched from fate and returned to family Masterson! You see, Agnes? We Mastersons get things done!
A... reward. Well, I suppose that would be fair. It's better than not getting it back at all, I guess.
I suppose I could be convinced to pay a fair price. Here, take this bag of gold. I think you will find it quite accomodating.
Allow me to express my thanks, and my relief. Now, if you don't mind, we're off to celebrate.
We'll be all right. Bad things don't happen to our class of people.
I've no time for this. Goodbye.
What seems to be the trouble?
You paid with an amulet?
Who was this man?
I've no interest in helping you.
I won't help for free.
I could look into it for you.
What do you know about the docks?
Sorry, I haven't discovered anything yet.
I need you to repeat some things.
I have your amulet here.
That will be fine. Thank you.
